# Business Problem

### Dataset is multiple product categories

### The value represent the no of unit purchased by each clinet for each product 

## Aim is to make cluster from this dataset that can segment similar clients together 

### Based on their annual spending on diverse product like milk,grocery, region etc

### There are 441 customers and 6 products and 1 region and 1 channel

### build Hierarchical cluster using various measurements technique.

# import required libraries 

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

from sklearn.preprocessing import normalize
import sklearn.cluster.hierarchical as shc
from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering
import scipy.cluster.hierarchy as shc

# Load the data set 

df = pd.read_csv("Wholesale customers data.csv")

df.head()

There are multiple products like fresh, frozen, detergents_paper and delication are available.The value represents the unit purchased by different customers.

Normalize the data so that scale of each variable should same , so that my model could not be biased towards higher magnitude of dataset.

# Normalize data 

data_actual = normalize(df)

# Convert normalize data into Data frame 

data_scaled = pd.DataFrame(data_actual,columns=df.columns)

source: data_scaled.head()
data has been scaled between 0 to 1 and good to go draw dendogram to decide the nos of cluster.

plt.figure(figsize=(8,7))
plt.title("Dendrogram Chart")

dend = shc.dendrogram(shc.linkage(data_scaled,method="ward"))

x - axis comtain the sample data 
y - axis represents the distance between these squares 
vertical line with maximum distance is in blue color
we can decide the threshold '6' and cut the dendogram
Based on '6' threshold two ckuster will create because line will be cut on two places.
Apply Hierarchical clustering for two clusters

# Create Method for cluster 

cluster = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2,affinity='euclidean',linkage='ward')

# fit the cluster 

cluster.fit_predict(data_scaled)

# Create Method for cluster 

cluster1 = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2,affinity='euclidean',linkage='complete')

cluster.fit_predict(data_scaled)

# Create Method for cluster 

cluster = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2,affinity='manhattan',linkage='average')

cluster.fit_predict(data_scaled)

now we can see the cluster 0 and 1

0 - represents the points that belongs to first cluster 

1-  represents the points that belongs to second cluster

# Visualize the two clusters
# use scatter plot
plt.title("cluster used Euclidean distance and linkage is average")
plt.scatter(data_scaled['Milk'],data_scaled['Grocery'],c=cluster.labels_)
plt.show()

# Visualize the two clusters
# use scatter plot
plt.title("cluster used Euclidean distance and linkage is average")
plt.scatter(data_scaled['Fresh'],data_scaled['Grocery'],c=cluster.labels_)
plt.show()

# Visualize the two clusters
# use scatter plot
plt.title("cluster used Euclidean distance and linkage is complete")
plt.scatter(data_scaled['Milk'],data_scaled['Grocery'],c = cluster.labels_)
plt.show()
